🌲Parking nearby? There’s actually quite a lot of parking options 3-5 minute walking distance from the bus stop.

My family has suffered an unimaginable and heart-breaking loss. My 23-year old nephew, Josh, was killed in a horrific hit and run motorcycle accident this past Friday night. 

Josh was the sweetest kid with the cutest most contagious laugh. He always made our family parties more fun. He would walk in with the biggest smile and hug everyone so tight. He truly lived life to the fullest. His love for animals is what many will always remember him for. He saved and took care of all sorts of animals throughout his life and had finally made his business @goldenleash_pet_services an official NJ business at the beginning of this year. We were all so proud of him and always knew he was destined for greatness. I remember him asking for name ideas on our family chat and being so excited for his official venture. He was well known all over Hudson and Bergen County. 

I’ll never when he was around 2 years old andy cousin Susan (his mom) and I taking him everywhere with us back in the day. His love for his sister Aliyah was unmeasurable, they were attached at the hip. Always taking care of one another. Always protecting her🤍

The pain that my cousin is suffering at the loss of her only son is something I don’t wish on anyone. That phone call was the phone call no one wants to get.

This is just the beginning of the summer. Please be careful out there. Be mindful when you drive. Please watch for motorcycle drivers. If you have a motorcycle, I beg you to please think of your loved ones who worry about you daily. And last, please send prayers to his mom and his sisters; Aliyah & Leah🤍thank you to those who have DMd me and sent prayers our way.

I’m pretty sure I’ve never shared before and after pics of my house. I should start a little series because it’s truly a different home. I’m really good at visualizing a space even when it doesn’t look so pretty… I love the before and after of Emme’s room; it’s absolutely mg favorite room in the house. 

My favorite ways to revamp any rooms are:

+ Change the light fixture, I personally highly dislike basic lights. And I hate fans😭I know they are functional, they are just never cute IMO. A beautiful light fixture gives the room character. 
+ Remove the carpet🫠 We were lucky enough to have beautiful wooden floors under that dirty carpet. 
+ Paint, paint, plaint! And paint a neutral… it’s so much easier to update the room as the kids get older if you have a neutral base. I added @projectjunior 🦢decals to bring the room together. 
+ I have a weird obsession with removing doors from closets… it makes the room feel bigger. I also love to add wallpaper to the back wall of the closet to make it beautiful to look at.
+ Please get the 96” curtains! I adore how long ceiling to floor curtain panels look. So chic. These are from @target and they are velvet😍

I’m a big believer that you can create a beautiful room anywhere. No matter the size✨SAVE this post for inspo!

Ben turned 12 yesterday and he’s going to middle school this year. And to be honest, I’ve had a very hard time with my emotions lately and accepting that his a little man now. It’s so strange to have a tween and a toddler at the same time. The emotions of one going to middle school and the other headed for preschool… And course I’m grateful and feel blessed but yet it’s still so bittersweet🤍

As parents we spend 18 years of our lives raising this child in hopes that they become these happy successful adults. And we pray that most of all, we’ve done a great job at teaching them to be KIND to others and themselves🤍

Their entire childhood is like a rollercoaster of emotions and events. And still I’m only at the start of year twelve but in true perspective I’m also already more than half way through my “good ole days” with him. 

Now all of a sudden, he’s almost a teenager and i only have maybe another year or hard push on two before I’m no longer his favorite person. I can already feel it… and it’s hard🤍

But I spoke to a friend and she said exactly what I needed to hear… something along the lines of “mama, it IS hard but one day you’ll look at him and think ‘wow I made that’ and you’ll feel so proud”.

I told her how sad I felt to see my oldest grow up and think that he will soon leave me… to what she replied: “he’ll never leave you, they’re always gonna come back home because of how you raise him.  They are never really gone” 🤍

So the lesson I’m learning is that one day you look back and all the crazy chaotic messy loud moments are gone - so enjoy the “good ole days” now while they are little, right now while you are their everything🤍

I wanted to share this in case you needed to hear this too mama🤍

A lot of you asked where we were over the weekend…so here’s the scoop: 

We drove 2 hours down to Wildwood Crest and stayed at the Port Royal Hotel in an oceanfront suite🌊that’s how we got to witness a beautiful sunrise one morning… 

We stayed 3 days and it was perfect but i may have been able to do one more day. 

The hotel was nice, we stayed there for the location because it was beyond perfection! The lobby, the arcade, the pool, the restaurant were all 10s. But the rooms themselves felt small and outdated. But do keep in mind I’m a self proclaimed hotel snob💁🏻‍♀️🥲

I also didn’t loved that they didn’t have beach chairs and umbrellas for their guests. All hotels I’ve stayed at down the shore provide chairs and umbrellas for guests to cross over and hang out at the beach. Here you had to rent them at the beach.

Like I said though, we stayed for the location because there was so much to do nearby with kids. There’s a bike rental, playground and splash park all within a short walking distance. The boardwalk is about a 5-7 min drive. And there are tons of great restaurants around. 

But the main character here was the beautiful-shallow-watered-soft sand-stunning beach right across the hotel🌊

My goal is to find the prettiest beaches in NJ and this was definitely a W.

Blogging Tips: How to Create Connections on Social Media🤝

Create opportunities for yourself. Some of my best connections have been built on putting myself in front of brands and agencies. Whether in person or email introductions.

Network your little booty off! Make connections with people face to face and attend the events. And though I genuinely love going to events with friends, don’t be afraid to go alone. It gives you an opportunity to get to know new people and space for new connections, uninterrupted. If you are with friends, make sure to take some time to go around the room on your own too.

Don’t be afraid to pitch yourself and send out your media kit. Believe me, a DM goes a long way when you are looking for PR/Marketing contacts. Just be sure to do the formal introduction on email, not on IG. 

Build your confidence and stop worrying about what people think. Don’t be afraid to ask other content creators for help or advice if you’ve built a true connection with them. It’s ok to let others know they inspire you and ask them how the did it. Not everyone is willing to give you their time and advice but the worst they can say is no or ignore you 👻

Social Media Tips: BUILDING COMMUNITY✨

I strongly believe that the main reason for my success in social media has been the tight community that I have built over the years. When I first started blogging, I had no idea this would become be a monetizing platform. I don’t think anyone did but of course it’s really nice to make a living off social media these days. And it’s all because of YOU, my social media family. Community is key!

Here are some tips on how to build community on social media: 

+ Be authentic. There’s nothing more obvious than people that try too hard just to fit. Be yourself and find YOUR people. Authenticity will get you noticed and relatability will create your community. Think of the people you follow, why do you follow them? Create that. That feeling the people you follow give you. 
+ Build genuine connection. Make sure you take the time to engage and have real conversations with your audience. I reply to DMs and comments, as best as I can.
+ Be relatable. People want to relate at some level. They want to know that not everything is perfect and there’s a sense of relief when someone opens up to share the hard moments. Even though this is ultimately a business for me, I’ve always taken the time to share the not hard times too. I’ve shared my miscarriage. I’ve shared my mom’s stroke. I’ve shared my battle with anxiety, and I’ve shared how it is very hard to be a mother and wife sometimes. It’s important for us women to relate, to know that it’s ok to not be okay. And for me, it’s equally as important to share how you get right back up and do your best. 

So remember to be authentic and stop trying to follow trends just for the sake of it because it shows! And if you’re doing this only for the money, you’re starting off in the wrong foot. Focus on your passion and make a career out of something that you already LOVE to do. Find ways to monetize what you already enjoy and are good at. Good luck, xo.

#socialmediatips #contentcreatortips #socialmediaexpert #bloggingtips

Quick & Easy Arroz con Pollo🐥

This popular Latin dish is made different ways but this is how I make it, I try to simplify my life as much as possible and the secret ingredient is always LOVE! 

Ingredients:

Chicken Breasts
Yellow Rice
Butter
Peas & Carrots 
Onions (white or red)
Cilantro
Garlic Garlic Powder 
Adobo
Ground Pepper
Onion Powder
Soy Sauce
Avocados

Make yellow rice as you normally would, I personally like to use turmeric to color my rice. I don’t measure so just listen to your ancestors😉I’m sorry, but this is just from the heart and I taste as I go. 

Boil water with half an onion, ground pepper, garlic powder, adobo and onion powder. Once boiled add in chicken breast (I cut them up so they can cook faster). In a separate pot start to boil your peas and carrots.

In a skillet, add 2 tablespoons of your butter stick, let simmer then start adding chopped onions and garlic until sautéed. Mix, mix, mix! Add cooked peas and carrots and mix some more!

Once the chicken is cooked, shred the meat and add to your veggie mix. Add soy sauce to taste. Add your rice. Sprinkler your cilantro… and you are done! This can be served with avocados or maduros or both:) That’s it!
